title: Bug 121170 get column label from meta data object should return some user recognizable strings
OB: Calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before and after data extraction produces different results.
EB: IMetaData.getColumnLabel() should return the same labels before and after data extraction to ensure consistency when displaying labels to the end user.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, perform the following steps:
1. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction.
2. Extract the data.
3. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() after data extraction.
4. Compare the results of both calls to observe the difference.
